Scenario:
Design a corporate leave approval workflow. In this hierarchy, an employee's time-off request must be approved by different levels of management depending on the number of days requested.

Requirements:

Request Object: LeaveRequest containing the number of days and the employee's name.

Base Approver: LeaveApprover defining the contract for approval and setting the "successor."

Concrete Approvers:

TeamLead: Can approve leaves up to 2 days.

Manager: Can approve leaves up to 10 days.

CEO: Handles long-term leave requests or special cases.

Goal: Create a chain of command where each manager either processes the request or passes it to their superior if the request exceeds their authority level.